data.description: MTN VIEWS * OPEN AND BRIGHT * NEWER ROOF(2020) * REMODELED MASTER AND UPPER BATHROOM (2021)* BACKS TO 27 ACRES OF PRIVATE PASTURE * CUL-DE-SAC *  COMPOSITE DECK * RETRACTABLE AWNING *  2 FIREPLACES * NEUTRAL PAINT *VELUX SKYLIGHTS * STAINLESS APPLIANCES * BARN DOORS * 2 MASTER CLOSETS (1 UPDATED BY CLOSET BY DESIGN)* RADON SYSTEM * OUTDOOR GRILL    What a find nestled on a sweet lot backing to 27 acres of privately owned pasture.  You can appreciate all the specialness of privacy, mountain views and wildflowers to the rear of the property.  As you enter, you will instantly appreciate the open and bright concept with wonderful light, pitched ceiling in the great room, skylights and coveted wood floors.  The rooms flow beautifully into one another and there is an welcoming aesthetic to the entire main level.  The expansive composite deck with retractable awning and gas grill is the perfect spot to enjoy the Colorado weather and mountain views.    The elegant great room features neutral paint, wood burning fireplace with an electric insert and built-ins.  The dining room with windows all around overlooks the open space to the rear.  The well appointed kitchen boasts painted white cabinets, stainless appliances and pantry.  Meander to the second level and you will be dazzled by the master bedroom with a newly remodeled bathroom and master closet.  Barn doors adorn the second walk-in closet and entrance into the private master bathroom.  The other two bedrooms on this level share another completely remodeled bathroom.  The basement is a nice escape with loads of space.  Another large family room centered around the 2nd fireplace and enough space for a game area too.  Other special features include:  Mini splits for AC, hurricane resistant roof, composite wood floors in basement, main level study, newer lighting,  2 new water heaters (2020), new boiler (2020).  This home is close to parks, restaurants and Country Club of Colorado.
